Thorneochloa diegoensis

is found in Channel Islands (Santa Barbara County), San Diego, and Ventura Counties and Baja California, Mexico in rocky soil along vernal streams and canyons in chaparral and coastal sage-scrub vegetation; usually below 500 m (
Barkworth 2007
; 
Calflora 2018
).

