Spikelets with 1 floret (tribe 
Stipeae
); plants native or not

Plants not branching at the upper nodes, or with a few, flexible branches (

Pseudoeriocoma

); pedicels never plumose; species native, established introductions, or cultivated as ornamentals

Plants with woody, sometimes scandent bamboo-like culms, 3-6 mm thick below with ramified branching (usually, but sometimes absent in immature specimens of 

P. hirticulmis

) at the middle and upper nodes, with (2) 3 to 13 nodes
